"text":" The provisions of paragraphs (1) and (2) of this subsection [amending sections 3104 and 5108 of this title] shall not apply with respect to any position so long as the individual occupying such position on the day before the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":"] continues to occupy such position."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Director—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"“(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in establishing under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5108"},"text":"section 5108 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, the maximum number of positions which may be placed in GS–16, 17, and 18 of the General Schedule, and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"“(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in establishing under section 3104 of such title 5 the maximum number of scientific or professional positions which may be established,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"shall take into account positions to which subparagraph (A) of this paragraph applies.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/tIV/s415/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454, title IV, § 415(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1179"},"text":"92 Stat. 1179","children":[],"tail":", provided that the provisions of section 414(a)(3) are effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[References in laws to rates of pay for GS–16, 17, or 18, or to maximum rates of pay under General Schedule, to be considered references to rates payable under specified sections of this title, see section 529 [title I, § 101(c)(1)] of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/509"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–509","children":[],"tail":", set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5376"},"text":"section 5376 of this title","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
